Package: tidysynth
Title: A Tidy Implementation of the Synthetic Control Method
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Eric", family = "Dunford", role = c("aut",
        "cre"), email = "ed769@georgetown.edu", comment = c(ORCID =
        "0000-0003-3056-8687"))
Description: A synthetic control offers a way of evaluating the effect
        of an intervention in comparative case studies. The package
        makes a number of improvements when implementing the method in
        R. These improvements allow users to inspect, visualize, and
        tune the synthetic control more easily. A key benefit of a tidy
        implementation is that the entire preparation process for
        building the synthetic control can be accomplished in a single
        pipe.
